
Ranger Help for: glevels
========================

SUMMARY:
Rangers advance their guild level automatically by earning Ranger XP in
battle. Each guild level grants additional skill slots for learning new
abilities. Use 'rcost', 'radvance guild', or 'gscore ranger' to see progress.

Guild level cannot exceed your game level. So to reach guild level 5,
you must be at least game level 5. Maximum guild level is 15.

SLOTS PER GUILD LEVEL:
  Level  1:  4 slots       Level  9: 11 slots
  Level  2:  5 slots       Level 10: 13 slots
  Level  3:  5 slots       Level 11: 13 slots
  Level  4:  7 slots       Level 12: 15 slots
  Level  5:  7 slots       Level 13: 15 slots
  Level  6:  9 slots       Level 14: 17 slots
  Level  7:  9 slots       Level 15: 20 slots
  Level  8: 11 slots

You start with 2 base slots when joining, and guild level 1 grants 4
more immediately, for a maximum total of 163 slots across all 15 guild
levels.

RANK:
Your Ranger rank is derived from skill slots invested, not guild level:
  Novice     (0-9 slots)       Captain    (70-99 slots)
  Regular    (10-24 slots)     Commander  (100-129 slots)
  Veteran    (25-44 slots)     Warden     (130+ slots)
  Elite      (45-69 slots)

SKILL SCORES:
As you learn skills, three scores increase automatically:
  Wilderness  Based on Survival + Cartography + Hunting skills
  Martial     Based on Attack + Archery skills
  Spiritual   Based on Husbandry skills

These scores affect the power of your abilities. Type 'rscore' to
see your current scores and rank.

